[normal]Mifalot
[normal] operates a number of programs focused on peace and coexistence. The goal of these programs is to bring together 
[normal]different groups within the
[normal] diverse population
[normal]s in Israel and in the region including Jordan and Palestine. With all of these groups 
[normal]football 
[normal]b
[normal]ecomes a tool for bridging
[normal] social, religious and ethnic divides. Football 
[normal]is
[normal] the common ground that all people like and relate to. It helps individuals from opposing groups realize that they are not so different. From there, we use this common ground to ho
[normal]ld a dialogue about differences
[normal], coexistence, conflict mitigation
[normal] and how to understand and accept each other.
[normal]Mifalot's projects include the following:
[normal]-
[normal] 
[normal]Know Your Neighbor/Neighbor's United: Breaking down stereotypes and building trust - both on and off
[normal] the field - between youth from different groups within Israel and between Israelis, Palestinians and Jordanians.
[normal]-
[normal] 
[normal]Coaches for Social Change: Educating Palestinian and Israeli young adults together to be football coaches and peace educators and then sendi
[normal]ng them out into their communities to work as coaches with teams of youth.
